// What jsconfig.json gives you
// 	1.	Path auto-completion
// VS Code now recognizes your aliases (@components, @assets, etc.) and suggests them in IntelliSense.
// → You can type @c and it’ll suggest @components.
// 	2.	Go to definition / Peek definition
// You can Ctrl+Click or Cmd+Click an alias import (like @components/Button) and jump straight to that file.
// 	3.	Import auto-fixes
// When you move or rename files, VS Code updates alias imports correctly, rather than breaking with long relative paths.
// 	4.	Error highlighting & IntelliSense
// TypeScript/JS language service understands your project root, giving better type hints and “cannot find module” errors disappear.

{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["src/*"],
      "@assets/*": ["src/assets/*"],
      "@components/*": ["src/components/*"],
      "@pages/*": ["src/pages/*"],
      "@styles/*": ["src/styles/*"],
      "@utils/*": ["src/utils/*"]
    }
  }
}